The premise "Ampa, afei, mɛka akyerɛ wo." and the hypothesis "Enee afei, mɛka asɛm akyerɛ wo." have essentially the same meaning in Twi:

Premise: "Indeed, now, I will tell you."
Hypothesis: "Today now, I will tell you something."

Both sentences convey the idea that the speaker is about to tell the listener something at the present moment.
